INSTRUCTIONS

Overview

The goal of this lab is to introduce the basics of shiny, a package used to build apps in RStudio. shiny allows users to build interactive graphics to explore and tell stories with their data. Students should begin by exploring the shiny website â there are a lot of great resources and examples to explore.

Note

Shiny should be combined with another package, bslib which provides a modern UI toolkit for Shiny based on Bootstrap.

This labâs main objective will be to reinforce and slightly extend the shiny basics covered in lesson 1 and lesson 2. We slightly extend the material by using ggplot graphics instead of the base R graphics they use in their examples.

Dataset

To complete this lab we require the familiar cdc.txt dataset. As a reminder the dataset variables are

  • genhlth - How would you rate your general health? (excellent, very good, good, fair, poor)
  • exerany - Have you exercised in the past month? (1=yes, 0=no)
  • hlthplan - Do you have some form of health coverage? (1=yes, 0=no)
  • smoke100 - Have you smoked at least 100 cigarettes in your life time? (1=yes, 0=no)
  • height - height in inches
  • weight - weight in pounds
  • wtdesire - weight desired in pounds
  • age - in years
  • gender - m for male and f for female
